nodes.title: Note // About
widgets_values:
Module #3 // Compositing & Editing // About . . .
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
              >>>For Compositing and Editing<<<
-------------------------------------------------------------
-------------------------------------------------------------
This module handles a variety of tasks related to compositing and editing. 
-------------------------------------------------------------
Sound executes upon completion - be aware of the volume - it should be around 0.1 - which is low. (red node/playsound)
-------------------------------------------------------------
Important: Mute or bypass nodes further down the sequential line of a group to shorten generation times or to lessen v-ram usage by the generation.
-------------------------------------------------------------
In-Paint: Right Click Load Image node, select "Open in MaskEditor", Clear Image, Mask area you want to change, and Save to Node. It is recommended to use an in-paint model.
-------------------------------------------------------------
ClipSeg: Auto mask portions of the image to edit via text input using this.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Pix2Pix: You can download the controlnet pix2pix model using the comfy-ui manager Install Models tab. More info:
https://github.com/timothybrooks/instruct-pix2pix
-------------------------------------------------------------
Watermark Creation: 
Lora Download Link:
https://civitai.com/models/176555/harrlogos-xl-finally-custom-text-generation-in-sd
-------------------------------------------------------------
Simple Mask: a very basic way to create images using masks.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Gligen: 
https://comfyanonymous.github.io/ComfyUI_examples/gligen/
-------------------------------------------------------------
IPAdapter Attention Masking: You can download the IPAdapters models using the comfy-ui manager Install Models tab. You will need a mask with blue, red, and green values to use this. Example Image Mask:
https://imgur.com/a/lfR8d2G
-------------------------------------------------------------
IPAdapter Styler: Models available in Comfy-UI manager.
-------------------------------------------------------------
IpAdapter FaceID: Models available in Comfy-UI manager.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Image & Text Overlay: Many options for overlays.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Image Cropping: A variety of ways to crop images.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Image Border: A variety of ways to make borders.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Filters & Color Correction: Try it out.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Node Color Information and More Below:

nodes.title: Note // Extra Information
widgets_values:
Module #3 // Compositing & Editing // Extra Information . . .
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Easily switch between modules by using the 1, 2, 3, & 4 number keys on your keyboard.
-------------------------------------------------------------
All modules here are uniform and have a left-to-right, top-to-bottom flow (sequential flow). Meaning they read just like a book. No nodes are hidden and all similar or branching nodes are grouped together accordingly. This aims to solve the organizational problem that most other workflows have and to simplify the creation process.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Main model used - Dreamshaper 8: 
https://civitai.com/models/4384?modelVersionId=128713
-------------------------------------------------------------
All IPAdapter models can be found in the Comfy UI Manager Install Models tab. Type "faceid" in the search for quick picks. Update all if you run into further issues.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Experiment with different batch sizes for the "emptyimage // experimental settings" node for different results. The color value also has an added effect. I've also added more options for color modifications. This is experimental and you can bypass them if you don't like the results. 
-------------------------------------------------------------
For SDXL & LCM simply change models and parameters to match.
-------------------------------------------------------------
All nodes are locked - to move them you will need to "unlock" them via right click. For those who don't know the difference, locked nodes cannot be moved even with a group, while pinned nodes can still be moved with a group.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Trouble Shooting InsightFace:
If you experience this error: "No Module InsightFace"
Remove Reactor Nodes if you have them installed then manually install insightface. Follow the troubleshoot guide here:
https://github.com/Gourieff/comfyui-reactor-node#insightfacebuild
-------------------------------------------------------------

groups.title: Module #3 // ClipSeg // Use CLIPSeg to auto mask & modify specific parts of the image via text input // . . .
Module #3 // Pix2Pix // Use controlnet Pix2Pix & regular chat like language to convey the changes you want to make to the image // . . .
Module #3 // IPAdapter Attention Masking // Use this to combine 3 images into a single image using attention masking for subject control // . . .
Module #3 // In-Paint // Manually inpaint your image - right click - Open in MaskEditor - clear image - mask area - save to nodes // . . .
Module #3 // IPAdapter Styler // Use this to apply a style to your loaded image using the second image loader as the style combine // . . .
Module #3 // Filters & Color Correction // Add or Adjust Color // . . .
Module #3 // Image & Text Overlay // Use this to overlay images & text // . . .
Module #3 // Image Border // Create borders for your images // . . .
Module #3 // Image Cropping // Use this to crop Images // . . .
Module #3 // Simple Mask // Add a mask image to the load image node to use a mask in your generation // . . .
Module #3 // IPAdapter FaceID // Use this as a face swapper - load your base image into the 1st loader & the face you want to add into the 2nd image loader // . . .
Module #3 // GLIGEN // This lets you specify the location & size of a subject in the image // . . .
Module #3 // Watermark Creation // Create an image for your watermark or logo // . . .
